title: -Fast Neutron Scattering From Sn-120 and Gd.-

x4codes.shortRef: Prog: Japanese report to EANDC, No.22, p.10 (1971)

x4freetext: -FAST NEUTRON SCATTERING FROM SN-120 AND GD.-
JAERI 5.5 MV VAN DE GRAAFF ACCELERATOR AND
FOR NEUTRON ENERGIES GREATER THAN 2 MEV AND
ABOUT 60 KEV FOR NEUTRON ENERGIES LESS
DETECTOR CONSISTED OF AN NE-213 LIQUID
12.0 CM FROM THE CENTRE OF THE GAS CELL TO THE
SCATTERER. THREE DETECTORS WERE PLACED IN 10 DEG.
STEPS AND MOUNTED ON A LARGE TURN TABLE WITH FLIGHT
.THE PEELING-OFF METHOD WAS APPLIED TO UNRESOLVED PEAKS
A.P.T. JAPAN CODE CHANGED TO JPN
.MULTIPLE SCATTERING AND ATTENUATION OF NEUTRON FLUX
IN THE SAMPLES, AND SOURCE-TO-SAMPLE GEOMETRICAL
.ERRORS ORIGINATING IN THE PEELING-OFF PROCESS WHEN IT
